# React Native Best Practice

Reference: [numandev1/react-native-best-practice](https://github.com/numandev1/react-native-best-practice)

---

## 1. Re-render Detection (Development)

Use **why-did-you-render** in `__DEV__` only. Import at app root (`index.js`):

```ts
import React from 'react';

if (__DEV__) {
  const whyDidYouRender = require('@welldone-software/why-did-you-render');
  whyDidYouRender(React, {
    trackAllPureComponents: true,
    trackHooks: true,
  });
}
```

---

## 2. Reference Equality & Memoization

- **Value types** (number, string, boolean): compared by value → `7 === 7` is true.
- **Reference types** (object, array, function): compared by reference → `{} === {}` is false.

Native components (`View`, `Text`, `Image`, etc.) pass props over the bridge. Unmemoized objects/functions cause new references every render → bridge traffic and unnecessary re-renders.

### Styles

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
return <View style={[styles.container, { backgroundColor: 'red' }]} />;

// ✅ GOOD
const style = useMemo(() => [styles.container, { backgroundColor: 'red' }], []);
return <View style={style} />;
```

**Exception:** Reanimated styles from `useAnimatedStyle` must be dynamic; do not memoize.

### Arrays (filter, map, etc.)

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
return <Text>{users.filter((u) => u.status === 'online').length} users online</Text>;

// ✅ GOOD
const onlineCount = useMemo(
  () => users.filter((u) => u.status === 'online').length,
  [users]
);
return <Text>{onlineCount} users online</Text>;
```

### Functions

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
return <View onLayout={(layout) => console.log(layout)} />;

// ✅ GOOD
const onLayout = useCallback((layout) => console.log(layout), []);
return <View onLayout={onLayout} />;
```

### Forward-propagating Functions

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
return <PressableOpacity onPress={() => props.logoutUser()} />;

// ✅ GOOD
return <PressableOpacity onPress={props.logoutUser} />;
```

### Objects

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
return <RecyclerListView scrollViewProps={{ horizontal: props.isHorizontal }} />;

// ✅ GOOD
const scrollViewProps = useMemo(
  () => ({ horizontal: props.isHorizontal }),
  [props.isHorizontal]
);
return <RecyclerListView scrollViewProps={scrollViewProps} />;
```

### Lift Out of Render (static values)

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
function MyComponent() {
  return <RecyclerListView scrollViewProps={{ horizontal: true }} />;
}

// ✅ GOOD
const SCROLL_VIEW_PROPS = { horizontal: true };
function MyComponent() {
  return <RecyclerListView scrollViewProps={SCROLL_VIEW_PROPS} />;
}
```

### Initial State (lazy init)

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
const [me, setMe] = useState(users.find((u) => u.id === myUserId));

// ✅ GOOD
const [me, setMe] = useState(() => users.find((u) => u.id === myUserId));
```

### React.memo

```jsx
// ❌ BAD
export const MyComponent = (props) => <View>...</View>;

// ✅ GOOD
const MyComponentImpl = (props) => <View>...</View>;
export const MyComponent = React.memo(MyComponentImpl);
```

Use `React.memo` when the component renders the same result given the same props. Don't overuse.

---

## 3. Deep Equality (recreated objects)

When dependencies are objects recreated each render, use deep-equality hooks:

```ts
import { useDeepEffect, useDeepMemo, useDeepCallback, useDeepLayoutEffect, useDeepImperativeHandle } from 'react-native-best-practice';

useDeepEffect(() => { /* ... */ }, [recreatedDeepObject]);
```

Utils: `isEqual`, `cloneDeep`.

---

## 4. Lists

- **Never use FlatList** for large lists.
- **Use FlashList** (Shopify) – recycling views, only renders visible items.

---

## 5. Navigation

Use **Native Stack** (`@react-navigation/native-stack`) – platform-native screen primitives, better performance than JS stack.

---

## 6. State Management

- **Redux:** Use [reselect](https://github.com/reduxjs/reselect) for memoized selectors.
- **React Context:** Use [use-context-selector](https://github.com/dai-shi/use-context-selector) so components only re-render when their selected value changes.
- **Recommended:** Recoil, Jotai, Zustand.

---

## 7. Refs & Child Imperative APIs

Use `ref` + `useImperativeHandle` to call child functions from parent instead of prop drilling or state lifting.

---

## 8. Storage, Buffer, Crypto, Big Number

| Use case        | Prefer                                                |
|-----------------|-------------------------------------------------------|
| Storage         | [react-native-mmkv](https://github.com/mrousavy/react-native-mmkv) – sync, fast, encryptable |
| Buffers         | [react-native-buffer](https://github.com/craftzdog/react-native-buffer) – C++/JSI, ~4x faster |
| Crypto          | [react-native-quick-crypto](https://github.com/margelo/react-native-quick-crypto) – C++, ~58x faster |
| Big numbers     | [react-native-bignumber](https://github.com/margelo/react-native-bignumber) – C++, ~330x faster than BN.js |

---

## 9. Image/Video Placeholders

Use [react-native-blurhash](https://github.com/mrousavy/react-native-blurhash) – server-side blurhash string + client placeholder.

---

## 10. Currency & Number Formatting

```js
// ~2x faster than calling toLocaleString each time
const formatter = new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { style: 'currency', currency: 'USD' });
formatter.format(1234.56);
```

---

## 11. Safe Area

Handle Safe Area with paddings (e.g. `contentContainerStyle={{ paddingBottom: safeAreaBottom }}`) instead of wrapping entire screens.

---

## 12. Custom Text Component

Never use raw `<Text>`. Create a typography abstraction (font, size, color) and an ESLint rule to warn on raw `Text`.

---

## 13. Logging & Debugging

- Use a **custom logger** with emojis/categories for easier scanning.
- **Remove `console.log`** in production (e.g. `babel-plugin-transform-remove-console`).
- **Dev:** Enable Perf Monitor (Dev Menu → Show Perf Monitor) to watch JS/UI framerates.

---

## 14. Performance Profiling

- [FLASHLIGHT](https://docs.flashlight.dev/) – Android performance score.
- [Profiling guide](https://www.callstack.com/blog/profiling-react-native-apps-with-ios-and-android-tools).

---

## 15. Disclaimer

Don’t prematurely optimize. `useMemo`/`useCallback` have a cost; use when the component complexity or dependency graph justifies it. **Benchmark before and after.**
